Distance to 37/F = (37 - 1) * 5 meters = 180 meters

Time to accelerate to 5 m/s = 5 seconds (as calculated in question 1)
Distance covered during acceleration = 12.5 meters

Remaining distance at constant speed = 180 meters - 12.5 meters = 167.5 meters
Time at constant speed = 167.5 meters / 5 m/s = 33.5 seconds

Total time to 37/F = 5 seconds + 33.5 seconds = 38.5 seconds

After stopping at 37/F, the elevator needs to travel the remaining distance to 40/F.

Remaining distance = 195 meters - 180 meters = 15 meters

Since the elevator is already at 5 m/s, it will decelerate to stop at 40/F.

