Distance covered during deceleration = 0.5 * Deceleration * Time^2 = 0.5 * 1 m/s^2 * (5 s)^2 = 12.5 meters

However, the remaining distance is only 15 meters, so the elevator will stop before reaching 5 seconds of deceleration.

